```sh
$ npm i --save @nestjs/common @nestjs/core @nestjs/platform-express @nestjs/swagger reflect-metadata rxjs stripe cors
$ npm i --save-dev @nestjs/cli @nestjs/schematics @nestjs/testing @types/cors @types/node typescript
```

2. Set up the basic Nest.js application
Once the required dependencies are installed, create a new Nest.js application.

```sh
$ npx nest new stripe-nestjs-app
```

3. Integrate Stripe
First, create an account on Stripe.com if you don't already have one. Next, navigate to the [API keys page](https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys) and get your API keys (a publishable key and a secret key), which will be needed to integrate Stripe with the Nest.js application.

4. Configure the Stripe module
Create a new Nest.js module to handle all Stripe-related functionality. In the `src` folder, create a new folder named `stripe`, and then create a file named `stripe.module.ts` within it.

In `stripe.module.ts`, do the following to set up and configure the Stripe module:

```ts
import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';
import { ConfigModule } from 'projects/components/common/config/config';
import { Stripe } from 'stripe';
import { StripeController } from './stripe.controller';
import { StripeService } from './stripe.service';

@Module({
  imports: [],
  controllers: [StripeController],
  providers: [
    {
      provide: 'STRIPE',
      useFactory: () => new Stripe(process.env.STRIPE_SECRET, { apiVersion: '2020-08-27' }),
    },
    StripeService,
  ],
  exports: ['STRIPE', StripeService],
})
export class StripeModule {}
```

